U.S. President Joe Biden on Thursday signed into law a legislation that bans imports from China's Xinjiang region over allegations of forced labor. The U.S. accusations lack any credible evidence and rely on a series of slanders by extremists. In the name of "human rights", the United States is actually suppressing Xinjiang's economy, thus undermining China's stability. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Guan Xin explains.